de.targodan.usb

Class Version

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.targodan.usb.Version

  • public class Version
extends java.lang.Object
    Version represents a version as defined in semantic versioning SemVer providing methods to parse and compare versions.

    • Method Detail

      • parse

        public static Version parse(java.lang.String versionString)
        Parse parses the given version string to create a Version instance. The format is "[v]MAJOR.MINOR[.PATCH][-SUFFIX]" with the elements in brackets being optional.
        Parameters:
        versionString - The string representation of the version.
        Returns:
        The parsed Version
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the string could not be parsed.

      • getLatestVersionFromGithub

        public static Version getLatestVersionFromGithub()
        This method will look up the latest released version on GitHub. It will block until the result is in. NOTE: pre-releases will be ignored.
        Returns:
        The latest version released on GitHub.

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        ToString returns a string representation of the Version. The format is "vMAJOR.MINOR[.PATCH][-SUFFIX]" with the elements in brackets being omitted if empty.
